info:
Responsibilities:
• Conducting legal research and daily dynamic tracking of laws, regulations and public policies;
• Providing assistance in preparing legal documents and contract review;
• Providing assistance in general corporate and IP matters;
• Assisting with Chinese/English translation of legal documents;
• Providing word-processing and secretarial support; and
• Assisting with administrative matters (such as archive of documents, preparation of workshop and training);
• Providing assistance in other ad hoc assignments.

Requirements:
• Undergraduate or postgraduate students;
• Strong research and analytical abilities;
• Fluent in both oral and written English;
• Proficient knowledge in MS Office (word, excel, PowerPoint);
• Team player, high degree of self-motivation, stress resistant and willingness to learn.

主要职责Key
Responsibilities 


	1. You will help to check the DA filings, which
include checking of the signing date, signing person (name and title);
re-scanning the twisted pages if any; compiling a PDA check list; updating the
PDA Index on a regular basis;


	2. You will help to check the board related
filings, which include filing the board related documents on a regular basis; compiling
the board related check list; coordinating with relevant person on the execution
of relevant board documents;


	3. You will help with any simple lease preparation
which does not require legal review;


	4. You will review NDAs and maintain NDA database;


	5. You will manage corporate certificates,
distribute the certificate to the requested Dept. and keep records;


	6. You will help to prepare for the materials for
certificates/licenses renewal and submit the materials to relevant competent
authority government.





	资格要求Required
Qualifications 


	 - Undergraduate or postgraduate, major in Law
preferred; 


	 - Can work 5 days fulltime per week preferred; 


	 - Good communication and coordination skill; 


	 - Good oral and written English skill; 


	 - Nice personality.

Accountabilities:
• Legal research and summary;
• Translation of legal documents;
• Drafting simple legal documents;
• Other supporting tasks assigned by the manager.

Qualifications:
1.   Law School Background. Master Degree is a plus.
2.   Relevant working experience in law firm and multinational company is a plus.
3.   Strong sense of responsibility and concentration. Well-organized.

阳狮集团诚招HR实习生： 

Role：HR Intern(Recruitment)

Job Responsibilities: 
• Support intern recruitment and campus program; 
• Check and record management by scanning important documents; 
• Documents filing and maintenance; 
• Support on harmonization activities and related paper work which assigned by the HR team; 
• Support HR for other daily operation issues; Requirements；
• Attendance: at least 4 days per week/at least for 3 months; 
• Bachelor degree or above, prefer student who will graduate in 2026 and majoring in HR or Management related; 
• Smart and responsible, good at communication/collaboration, good team player; 
• Good written and fluent English, good application in MS office tool: word, excel and PPT；
